<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / Attack on NHS bureaucracy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TOO MANY managers' jobs have been created under the government's health
service reforms, Mr Ivan Lester, retiring chairman of Harrogate Health Care
Trust, said yesterday.
He told BBC Radio: 'We have put extra layers of bureaucracy, of management,
in and we actually don't know if we are getting any more healthcare out of
this so-called market.'
Sir Duncan Nichol, health service chief executive, said: 'I believe we
should not be talking about the bureaucratic overhead here; we should be
talking about the benefits that management have brought to the health
service.'
