<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / Staff at Yarrow to return to work
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WHITE-COLLAR workers on strike at the Yarrow warship yard on the Clyde voted
yesterday to return to work, having successfully fought off an attempt to
introduce performance-related pay for 500 draughtsmen and supervisory staff.
The staff walked out two weeks ago in protest at a pay offer of 1.8 per cent
plus a performance-linked rise of up to 2.6 per cent.
Yesterday's deal gives all white-collar staff a general increase of 2.5 per
cent. Officials of the MSF technical union said performance-related pay
would never work in the shipbuilding industry.
Yarrow, part of the GEC group, has orders for three warships for the Royal
Navy and for two more for the Malaysian navy.
