<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 93 / Nintendo shows signs of slowdown
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NINTENDO, Japan's leading manufacturer of video games, yesterday showed the
first signs of a slowdown after 10 years, when it announced interim pre-tax
profits 24 per cent lower than a year ago at Y61.07bn (Dollars 566.2m),
compared with Y80.25bn, on sales that were 6.2 per lower at Y260.18bn. The
forecast for the full year to March is no better, with a pre-tax profit of
Y121bn on sales of Y500bn expected, compared with Y163.80bn and Y562.70bn
respectively.
Analysis, Page 23
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Nintendo.
</CO>
