himself as a man committed to freer trade and liberal trade on a global
basis.'
Apec delegates had been at pains to point out a bright side for their
organisation whether Nafta won or lost. Mr Philip Burdon, New Zealand's
minister for trade negotiations, said that while Apec would complement
Nafta, in the event of failure it would have become a fallback position.
