<TEXT>
MEXICAN equities ended higher after an erratic session characterised
alternately by strong demand and profit-taking after Wednesday's US approval
of Nafta. The IPC index gained 17.68 at 2,166.18 after veering between
2,145.52 and 2,174.51. Some analysts expect the market to rise 30 per cent
by next March.
