FT  19 NOV 93 / Finance director at Independent is asked to resign
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE INDEPENDENT newspaper has asked for the resignation of Ms Suzanna
Taverne, its finance director, Raymond Snoddy writes.
Ms Taverne, who was appointed finance director in March 1992, is eight
months pregnant and was about to take maternity leave. The Independent is an
Opportunity 2000 employer - part of the campaign to boost the position of
women in the workplace.
It is believed that Ms Taverne, who joined The Independent in 1990 from
merchant bank SG Warburg as a strategic planning executive, was told that
her job was to be offered to Mr Graham Luff, managing director of Newspaper
Publishing, the company that publishes both The Independent and the
Independent on Sunday.
The changes flow from a restructuring of management following the arrival of
Mr Patrick Morrissey as chief executive.
Mr Luff, a qualified accountant, is now expected to return to the finance
role while Ms Taverne has been offered the opportunity of working out her
one-year notice at the paper in her original post of strategic planning. It
is believed she is in negotiations over severance terms.
