<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 93 / World News in Brief: Minibus death toll rises
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tighter safety laws on coaches and minibuses were urged after the death toll
in a school minibus crash on the M40 in Warwickshire rose to 12. A teacher
and 10 pupils were killed instantly. Another pupil died later of her
injuries.
